## Instructions

1. Read all Markdown files in `/context-repo/` to understand the project's guidelines.
2. Review the PR diff by running `git diff origin/{{ base_branch }}...HEAD` in `/workspace`.
3. Ignore all files under the `.smithy/` directory — these are internal working files, not part of the deliverable.
4. Evaluate the changes against the guidelines in the context repository.
5. Include references to context repo guidelines as clickable relative links in the format:
   `[Section Name](/{{ owner }}/{{ context_repo }}/src/branch/main/filename.md#section-id)`

## Output

- `summary`: Your overall review as markdown-formatted text. Use actual line breaks for formatting — do not use escape sequences. Keep it short and concise.
- `comments`: Inline comments for specific files and lines. Each has `path` (relative to repo root), `line` (line number in HEAD version, must appear in the diff), and `body` (markdown-formatted comment text). May be empty if no line-specific comments.

- Keep your output short and concise, it is a comment on a pull request.
- Use limited formatting, only where it adds value.
- Only comment about things that violate the guidelines or are very clearly bugs.
- Do not comment about small things.

- Do not write descriptive text about the pull request itself. Assume that all readers involved are professionals that have read the code themselves.
